            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Sounds like a new 'buftype' could make sense. Or maybe there is an existing buftype(s) that LSP should already support (by updating the above condition).\n\nI think we do need to have a feature-rich user-facing type, and a blank-slate utility type.\n\nMaking a new `buftype` seems to be the most straightforward solution, if there are no worries about backwards compatibility. All of my scripts focus on checking that `buftype` is empty. I have no idea if that set of values is historically stable.\n\nAlternatively, if provided with enough localopts, users could combine things on their own, the same way `special-buffers` combine options into ephemeral concepts of \"directory\" and \"scratch\". But there is a challenge of making options apply at the right time, and making them cover very specific domains (`:setlocal nolspable` ðŸ˜‚).",
